FINAL PLAN OF ACTION (Step-by-Step) 

This is what you should actually do to start working on this use case  

Phase 1: Foundation Setup (Week 1–2) 

Actions: 

Identify:  

Source systems (mainframe, DB, files) 

Target system (OLB / unified system) 

Collect:  

Sample data files 

Copybooks / schemas 

Business rules 

Tools to use: 

Azure Storage / Data Lake 

SQL Server / Snowflake (if needed) 

Goal: 

Prepare real data + schemas for testing 

Phase 2: Data Understanding (Week 2–3) 

Actions: 

Build Data Profiling module 

Record counts 

Null values 

Data distribution 

Feed schemas + data into Mistral AI 

Output: 

Data profiling report 

Schema interpretation 

Why: 

You cannot reconcile data if you don’t understand it first 

 

Phase 3: AI Mapping + Rule Generation (Core Phase) 

Actions: 

Use Mistral to: 

Generate Source → Target mappings 

Convert business rules into logic 

Store mappings in: 

JSON / DB table 

Use Copilot for: 

Auto-generating:  

Mapping code 

Transformation scripts 

Goal: 

Automatically generate STTM (Source to Target Mapping) 

 

Phase 4: Build Execution Engine (Critical) 

Actions: 

Develop .NET services: 

Data ingestion 

Transformation 

Comparison 

Use: 

Pandas (small data) 

Spark (large data / scalability) 

Logic: 

Apply transformations 

Compare:  

Record count 

Field values 

Aggregates 

 Goal: 

 Execute reconciliation end-to-end 

Phase 5: Reconciliation & Validation Engine 

Actions: 

Implement checks:  

Count validation 

Field-level matching 

Aggregation checks 

Referential integrity 

Important: 

Add deterministic rules (non-AI checks) 
Do NOT rely only on AI 

 

Phase 6: Reporting & Audit 

Actions: 

Generate: 

Matched records 

Mismatches  

Missing data  

Data anomalies  

Store logs in: 

Azure Monitor / Log Analytics 

Goal: 

Full traceability + audit compliance 

 

Phase 7: Automation (Azure Pipelines) 

Actions: 

Build pipelines for:  

Data ingestion 

AI processing 

Execution 

Reporting 

Goal: 

Fully automated reconciliation flow 

 

